---
title: Homemade Vegetable Packed Calzone
description: We’re really excited to get you making the HelloFresh calzone! Our good friends at The Northern Dough Company have made this beautiful pizza dough in advance, so that all you need to do is roll
it out, top it with tastiness, fold it in half and bake it in your (pizza) oven. Make sure to cook this meal first this week so you get the dough at its absolute freshest!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/homemade-vegetable-packed-calzone-39e7a963.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/homemade-vegetable-packed-calzon-87c7da36.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 620 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 60 g
  protein: 31 g
servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/homemade-vegetable-packed-calzone-577ceb3fb2baafcd7c8b4568
---

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Peel and chop the @red onion{1} into
bite-sized chunks. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop into 3cm
chunks. Chop the leafy green part and the base from the @leek{1}, then chop
it widthways into 1cm thick discs. Chop the @cherry tomatoes{1} in half.

Toss your vegetables in a glug of @olive oil{glug} and a good pinch of
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook them on a #baking tray{} in your oven
for ~{20%minutes}.

Dust your work surface with the @flour{6}, roll each @Northern Dough Co. pizza
dough{2} out into a round pizza shape roughly 25cm across and place on a
lightly oiled baking tray.

> Tip: If you don't have a rolling pin you can always use a wine bottle (or
> even a tin can at a push!).

Spread the @tomato purée{2} thinly over each pizza base, leaving a border of
around 2cm at the edge.

Once your veggies are soft, divide them between each pizza base (making sure
you only cover one half of each base, so you can fold the other half over). Turn
your oven to maximum temperature. Tear the @mozzarella{1} on top and sprinkle
over the @Italian style herbs{1.5}.

> Tip: To prevent the pizza base getting soggy, be careful not to add any excess
> water from the vegetables.

Run a wet finger around the border of each pizza then fold them over to create
your calzone! Press the edges down to seal and put on the top shelf of your
oven for ~{8-10%minutes}. Job done!